Wow, this place needs some real work. We ordered takeout from here on a Sunday night and ate at our house 1 block away. About an hour later we went back to grab a drink. It looked pretty slow but there was 4 people having a good time at the bar. We grabbed a table and ordered one round of drinks for the four of us.

The four other people at the bar claimed to be related to the owners and as we're finishing our first drink this one blonde haired Lady named Alexis claimed to be the owner and told us VERY abruptly that we needed to leave and that they closed two hours ago. I asked her how are we supposed to know that when we just got our drinks and no one told us anything? She abruptly said, well I just told you. And I said, well, that was just 10 seconds ago - can we finish our drinks? She said no you guys need to leave, we closed two hours ago. We weren't being loud or obnoxious - just minding ourselves and talking at the table. I told her how rude that was and she said she didn't care that they owned the place and we had to leave.

My brother lives two blocks away and I visit him often. Suffice it to say we will never be back!

reviews_data.review_text: Great place! Love the ambience!

TBD Kitchen recently underwent some changes, notably the installation of a black cage on the bar top meant for liquor storage. Unfortunately, this addition, though functional, has significantly impacted the overall ambiance and practicality of the space.

The choice to place the cage on the bar top, blocking the once-visible chalkboard, is questionable at best. What was once an open and inviting atmosphere now feels cramped and closed in. The cage, though serving its storage purpose, acts as an eyesore and distracts from the otherwise pleasing aesthetics of the establishment.

One of the major drawbacks is the reduced space for patrons at the bar. The addition of the cage seems to have taken away valuable seating room, making it feel congested and less accommodating than before. It's disheartening to witness a space that previously exuded openness and comfort now struggle under the weight of a poorly placed storage solution.

While the functionality of the cage is understood, its current placement compromises the overall customer experience. It not only obstructs the view of the chalkboard but also gives off an impression of a thoughtless design choice. Patrons, who once enjoyed the freedom of an open bar setting, are now confronted with an obstacle that hinders their overall enjoyment.

In conclusion, TBD Kitchen's recent addition might serve a practical purpose, but its impact on the overall atmosphere and customer experience cannot be ignored. Reconsidering the placement or finding an alternative solution that doesn't compromise the aesthetic and spaciousness of the bar area would undoubtedly enhance the dining experience for patrons.

My recent visit to TBD Kitchen in Lewisville, Texas, was an absolute delight, and I owe much of that to the incredible bartender, Kaya. From the moment we took our seats at the bar, Kaya's expertise and charm elevated our experience to new heights.

Kaya's cocktail creations were nothing short of extraordinary — each sip was a flavor-packed journey that showcased her skill and creativity. Her warm and engaging personality added a personal touch to the evening, making us feel like valued guests.

TBD Kitchen's inviting ambiance paired with Kaya's exceptional service made for a memorable night out. If you find yourself at TBD Kitchen, don't miss the opportunity to have Kaya craft your drinks; it's an experience you won't forget. Cheers to TBD Kitchen and the amazing Kaya for an evening well-spent!

I just had the most unforgettable night at TBD Kitchen, and I couldn't wait to share the experience! From the moment I stepped in, the place exuded a warm and welcoming vibe that set the stage for a fantastic evening.

Let me tell you about Kaya, the extraordinary bartender who made the night even more special. Her passion for mixology was evident in every cocktail she crafted. Trust me; she knows how to elevate your drink game. Kaya's friendly and engaging personality added a personal touch, making me feel like a valued guest.

Now, onto the food – each dish on TBD Kitchen's menu is a culinary masterpiece. The chef's dedication to using fresh, high-quality ingredients truly shines through. From appetizers to desserts, the flavors were exquisite, leaving me craving more.

TBD Kitchen has this effortlessly cool ambiance, making it the perfect spot for a laid-back night out. Kaya's skill behind the bar and the delectable food make this place a standout in the local scene. It's the kind of spot you'd want to keep coming back to.

I recently had the pleasure of dining at TBD Kitchen, and let me tell you, it was an experience that exceeded all expectations. From the moment I walked in, the inviting ambiance and warm decor set the stage for what turned out to be an unforgettable culinary adventure.

One of the standout features of TBD Kitchen was undeniably the exceptional service, and at the forefront of this outstanding service was the amazing bartender, Kaya. From the first greeting to the final farewell, Kaya's professionalism, knowledge, and genuine passion for mixology shone through, elevating our entire dining experience.

Kaya's cocktail creations were nothing short of extraordinary. Each drink was meticulously crafted, showcasing a perfect balance of flavors and a creative flair that left me in awe. Whether you're a cocktail connoisseur or just looking to try something new, trust Kaya to guide you through a selection that caters to your taste preferences.

Beyond the impressive libations, Kaya's personality truly made the day special. Her warmth, attentiveness, and engaging conversation added a personal touch that is often hard to find. It's evident that Kaya takes pride in her work and genuinely cares about ensuring every guest has a memorable time at TBD Kitchen.

The menu at TBD Kitchen further solidified the establishment as a culinary gem. From appetizers to desserts, each dish was a testament to the chef's dedication to using fresh, high-quality ingredients. The diverse menu caters to a range of palates, and the chef's innovative twists on classic dishes left my taste buds dancing with delight.

Whether you're a local resident or just passing through, TBD Kitchen is a must-visit dining destination, and Kaya's expertise as a bartender is the proverbial cherry on top. Her skills, combined with the restaurant's delectable offerings, create an experience that goes beyond a simple meal — it's a journey through culinary excellence.

In conclusion, TBD Kitchen has earned its place as a top-tier dining establishment, and Kaya's presence behind the bar adds an extra layer of magic to the overall experience. Don't miss the opportunity to savor fantastic food, delightful drinks, and the outstanding hospitality provided by Kaya at TBD Kitchen. Cheers to an unforgettable dining adventure!

The way this restaurant is set up is just weird IMHO.  You walk through the door wondering if you ended up in the back service area. Its busy & loud & crowded & its the only way through the restaurant, so you maneuver through that food service area, trying not to get in the way, thinking you'll find the hostess stand at the other end.  Nope. So you navigate back to the food service area to find out you seat yourself.

Upon seating yourself, service is attentive & prompt.  They ran out of all the specials, so I ordered the carne asada, which was quite tender.  Its a family friendly restaurant, so if you want to be able to hear & talk with your dining party, this may not be the best setting.

Food - 4 stars
Atmosphere - 2 stars

Ordered Chicken Fajitas and a side of the brussel sprouts to go 45 min ago. Just got home to realize they didn’t give me tortillas - oh well, that happens. However, The chicken tasted very bland, which means it was not marinated at all. The guacamole had chips broken in it, which means someone in the kitchen was dipping into it - gross!! And it was just mashed up avocado with no spices added and it was brown which means it wasn’t fresh. Very disappointed especially when I spent $25 for the order!  The brussel sprouts were tasty, but not worth $25. While I was waiting for the order, a male employee entered carrying a bag and announced “I’m going to eat my sh*t before I clock in”. It appeared to be all young kids running the place. I’ve been in the restaurant business for 30 years so these observations are based on my experience. Too bad, but I won’t return. It’s a cute little restaurant but needs some quality control. This was at 4:30 on a Friday evening.

I’m very happy to say that within 30 minutes of posting my review, I was contacted by Manager, Sean. He apologized for what I experienced and offered to deliver another order to my home. When the food arrived, it was hot, tortillas included, and the chicken was flavorful and cooked/marinated to perfection. This kind of response and ownership truly shows he cares about his guests. I was extremely impressed and pleased. I wish more restaurants showed this kind of concern. I will return and I’ll tell my friends!  Thanks, Sean.
Great food and atmosphere! Everyone in the staff is amazing.
When you are at the entrance they are welcoming you with a big smile and a greeting what a nice people . The food here are so fantastic! Its so satisfying i love it!

Dine here often, I find myself craving TBD! It’s not only the food, but the drinks and atmosphere. The Surf and Turf is not your usual Chili Renello, it’s filled with deliciousness of grilled vegetables, rice, shrimp and beef cooked to perfection. Guacamole with spicy jalapeño and roasted brussels sprouts are the perfect shareables.

The chili relleno and steak was really good. I was a little sceptical when I got the plate, but the flavors were amazing! Also, they have some good beers at a good price. Also the molé old fashion was really good. It is basically an old fashioned with chocolate, so it is great!

Don’t go here if you want Latin food or even good food. I am appalled this restaurant has such high ratings because I was extremely disappointed. It serves overpriced bland Tex-Mex food. The “street tacos” were not flavorful, the rice was extremely dry with no flavor, and the quesadillas were over powered with pineapples that did not go well with the bland shrimp. The margarita was basic and expensive for what you get. To top it off, they charge you $2 for a small side of pico that literally had a few chunks of tomatoes in it (note the tacos are only $3). I have never written a review but the food was so bad I felt the need to write this to warn others.

Simply the best bars in the suburb that is Carrollton. From the amazing bartenders to the unique cocktails and beers to the quick bite foods or full five star meals. The music and vibes of the great patrons here make it a place that makes me want to come again and again.

Some of my favorites:
Elotes (corn on a cup with seasoning)
Gaviota (similar to Paloma cocktail with mezcal instead)
Campechanos (two tasty meats in one taco)
Four corners shandy (poblano mixed with el chingon)
Mango or strawberry frozen margaritas (bc duh)
Sunday morning there ain’t nothing better. Best Chilaquiles I’ve ever had. Waitress was also super nice and attentive! Will be coming back for sure :)

Absolutely fantastic place to grab some street tacos. Their “posh tacos” rotate seasonally, but the ones I have tried are amazing. Highly recommend the brisket taco if they have it, as well as the fried avocado. I was really impressed with the corned beef taco for St Patrick’s Day, hopefully that one can make more frequent appearances.

The table salsa is pretty good, but you definitely need to order some guacamole as well. The jalapeños pickles in soy sauce are a game changer. Everyone at the table agreed that the salsa verde was exceptional; I preferred the smoky orange salsa, but it is quite spicy (if that isn’t your thing).

Definitely our new favorite place for tacos. It doesn’t hurt that the ambience is also spot on.
Nice little spot next to PIE in Castle Hills Village Shops. The street tacos and original drinks make it a fun nighttime stop.
Great local place for street tacos. Pro tip--try their fried chicken

The cocktails are amazing and super creative.  We love to go for taco Tuesday... $2 street tacos.  I crave the carnitas!!  If it's not a Tuesday, we go for the fajitas, they're top notch!
Patio roof leaks, chips were oily and didn't have any salt, drinks were fine, but nothing to write home about

I would give it 3.5 stars if I could but the review doesn't let me do that. I  am leaning towards a 4 rather than a 3.

Good:
1) Cocktail (with rum, a few other ingredients, and coconut ice cube) was amazing.
2) Drinks have a decent amount of alcohol.
3) On the first visit, all the tacos (Baja Mahi Mahi, Cactus which we ordered without meat, Fried Avacado) were delicious.
4) Staff are friendly.
5) Not very crowded (perhaps due to the location).

Bad:
1) Appetizer plates and dishes were not cleared before the tacos arrived (on both visits).
2) Water was not refilled.
3) On our second visit, the tacos tasted just OK. I didn't expect the quality to differ so much in less than 10 days.
4) Salsa tasted like pasta sauce from a bottle. Some coriander was mixed in, perhaps to look like it was freshly made.

Could be better:
1) Guacamole was average at best, not worth the price.
2) On the first visit, 4 chips were included with the guac because they were still making the chips. They could have simply apologized and brought the guac after the chips were ready. They did bring in more chips later.
3) On our second visit, we could not order the desired cocktail because they were out of coconut ice cube on Saturday night at 7pm!
Fun environment and excellent drinks!

My wife and I love eating and having drinks here! My two year old daughter loves the patio she and other kids are usually exploring the patio just having a good time, very family friendly most of the day.  If you go later at night, music gets louder and people are out just having a great time socializing.

Please get the Aguachiles as an appetizer! Your welcome.!

Food was fresh and bottomless mimosas were great. Laid back casual spot with changing chefs menu and special drink every week.

Expensive, small portions and slow service

Their tacos are amazing and only $2 each on Taco Tuesday!!
Wow! Great patio with a view, dog friendly. Guacamole made fresh, chips seemed like made in house too, delicious. Drinks and entrees were great too. Everything was fresh, and fried yucca was perfect!

reviews_data.review_text: There was no flavor in the food.
Great local spot with amazing crowd
Great place for Mexican food w/Latin American twist. Taco Tuesdays are busy! They also have happy hours. Check it out!

The Latin wings were sooo good and I highly recommend. Chips weren’t hot and tasted stale. We got breakfast tacos that were mediocre. We were recommended the house Margarita and it did not disappoint. Overall an average experience.
Best place..EVERY Tuesday!!!
Margaritas hit hard, food is always solid, and our server Eddie is always top notch!
This is a super hidden gem. Great margaritas, had the loaded nachos, they were great. It is hard to notice...since its next door to Pie 314. Highly recommend this place.

The way this restaurant is set up is just weird IMHO.  You walk through the door wondering if you ended up in the back service area. Its busy & loud & crowded & its the only way through the restaurant, so you maneuver through that food service area, trying not to get in the way, thinking you'll find the hostess stand at the other end.  Nope. So you navigate back to the food service area to find out you seat yourself.

Upon seating yourself, service is attentive & prompt.  They ran out of all the specials, so I ordered the carne asada, which was quite tender.  Its a family friendly restaurant, so if you want to be able to hear & talk with your dining party, this may not be the best setting.

Food - 4 stars
Atmosphere - 2 stars
Great Taco Tuesday + Margaritas

Ordered Chicken Fajitas and a side of the brussel sprouts to go 45 min ago. Just got home to realize they didn’t give me tortillas - oh well, that happens. However, The chicken tasted very bland, which means it was not marinated at all. The guacamole had chips broken in it, which means someone in the kitchen was dipping into it - gross!! And it was just mashed up avocado with no spices added and it was brown which means it wasn’t fresh. Very disappointed especially when I spent $25 for the order!  The brussel sprouts were tasty, but not worth $25. While I was waiting for the order, a male employee entered carrying a bag and announced “I’m going to eat my sh*t before I clock in”. It appeared to be all young kids running the place. I’ve been in the restaurant business for 30 years so these observations are based on my experience. Too bad, but I won’t return. It’s a cute little restaurant but needs some quality control. This was at 4:30 on a Friday evening.

I’m very happy to say that within 30 minutes of posting my review, I was contacted by Manager, Sean. He apologized for what I experienced and offered to deliver another order to my home. When the food arrived, it was hot, tortillas included, and the chicken was flavorful and cooked/marinated to perfection. This kind of response and ownership truly shows he cares about his guests. I was extremely impressed and pleased. I wish more restaurants showed this kind of concern. I will return and I’ll tell my friends!  Thanks, Sean.
Great food and atmosphere! Everyone in the staff is amazing.
When you are at the entrance they are welcoming you with a big smile and a greeting what a nice people . The food here are so fantastic! Its so satisfying i love it!
Cool place, great artwork on the walls. Food was amazing, roasted brussel sprouts were incredible!

Dine here often, I find myself craving TBD! It’s not only the food, but the drinks and atmosphere. The Surf and Turf is not your usual Chili Renello, it’s filled with deliciousness of grilled vegetables, rice, shrimp and beef cooked to perfection. Guacamole with spicy jalapeño and roasted brussels sprouts are the perfect shareables.
Great service and the Cuban sandwich was very good 😊

That was all it took for me to get up after a long day and say lead the way. It was 7PM Tuesday night. We didn’t have to wait. That’s a plus. The staff was super awesome to some of our requests. I wanted an extra shot of tequila. Beth had the mango margarita which I hear was the bomb. We had a plan. We were going  to have one of each of the tacos apiece. None of them disappointed. I would however advise caution with the chorizo. All and all I give this place a 10. Sugar skulls adorned. Alissa is our favorite waitress when we come in. I just don’t have enough good things to say about this place.

Delicious house margaritas. Tacos were out of this world. Will definitely be back.
Awesome bartender/manager (Bree) makes amazing drinks and is super friendly and the kitchen serves top notch street tacos and other dishes.

They have a good bar scene at night as well if you’re into that.
Great tasting food and services, but portions are quite small and very expensive.

They have great good at a great price! We have been a few times and the burrito it's really good. It is really meaty and cheesy. I like that they put some extra cheese in it! The chili relleno and steak was really good. I was a little sceptical when I got the plate, but the flavors were amazing! Also, they have some good beers at a good price. Also the molé old fashion was really good. It is basically an old fashioned with chocolate, so it is great!

Don’t go here if you want Latin food or even good food. I am appalled this restaurant has such high ratings because I was extremely disappointed. It serves overpriced bland Tex-Mex food. The “street tacos” were not flavorful, the rice was extremely dry with no flavor, and the quesadillas were over powered with pineapples that did not go well with the bland shrimp. The margarita was basic and expensive for what you get. To top it off, they charge you $2 for a small side of pico that literally had a few chunks of tomatoes in it (note the tacos are only $3). I have never written a review but the food was so bad I felt the need to write this to warn others.

Simply the best bars in the suburb that is Carrollton. From the amazing bartenders to the unique cocktails and beers to the quick bite foods or full five star meals. The music and vibes of the great patrons here make it a place that makes me want to come again and again.

Some of my favorites:
Elotes (corn on a cup with seasoning)
Gaviota (similar to Paloma cocktail with mezcal instead)
Campechanos (two tasty meats in one taco)
Four corners shandy (poblano mixed with el chingon)
Mango or strawberry frozen margaritas (bc duh)
Sunday morning there ain’t nothing better. Best Chilaquiles I’ve ever had. Waitress was also super nice and attentive! Will be coming back for sure :)

Absolutely fantastic place to grab some street tacos. Their “posh tacos” rotate seasonally, but the ones I have tried are amazing. Highly recommend the brisket taco if they have it, as well as the fried avocado. I was really impressed with the corned beef taco for St Patrick’s Day, hopefully that one can make more frequent appearances.

The table salsa is pretty good, but you definitely need to order some guacamole as well. The jalapeños pickles in soy sauce are a game changer. Everyone at the table agreed that the salsa verde was exceptional; I preferred the smoky orange salsa, but it is quite spicy (if that isn’t your thing).

Definitely our new favorite place for tacos. It doesn’t hurt that the ambience is also spot on.

Patio roof leaks, chips were oily and didn't have any salt, drinks were fine, but nothing to write home about

I would give it 3.5 stars if I could but the review doesn't let me do that. I  am leaning towards a 4 rather than a 3.

Good:
1) Cocktail (with rum, a few other ingredients, and coconut ice cube) was amazing.
2) Drinks have a decent amount of alcohol.
3) On the first visit, all the tacos (Baja Mahi Mahi, Cactus which we ordered without meat, Fried Avacado) were delicious.
4) Staff are friendly.
5) Not very crowded (perhaps due to the location).

Bad:
1) Appetizer plates and dishes were not cleared before the tacos arrived (on both visits).
2) Water was not refilled.
3) On our second visit, the tacos tasted just OK. I didn't expect the quality to differ so much in less than 10 days.
4) Salsa tasted like pasta sauce from a bottle. Some coriander was mixed in, perhaps to look like it was freshly made.

Could be better:
1) Guacamole was average at best, not worth the price.
2) On the first visit, 4 chips were included with the guac because they were still making the chips. They could have simply apologized and brought the guac after the chips were ready. They did bring in more chips later.
3) On our second visit, we could not order the desired cocktail because they were out of coconut ice cube on Saturday night at 7pm!
Fun environment and excellent drinks!

My two year old daughter loves the patio she and other kids are usually exploring the patio just having a good time, very family friendly most of the day.  If you go later at night, music gets louder and people are out just having a great time socializing.

Please get the Aguachiles as an appetizer! Your welcome.!
